/////How to Create a Post on Facebook Page///////

On your page (via Facebook):

- Go to your Facebook Page
- Click “Create Post” / “What’s on your mind?”
- Add:
  a. Text (your message)
  b. Image / Video
  c. Link (if you have portfolio or website)
- Click Post

For Image
------------
For 2026, the recommended Facebook post size for maximum engagement is 1080 x 1350 pixels (4:5 ratio), 
as vertical content dominates feed visibility. 

Ideal image posts are 1080 x 1080 (square) or 1080 x 1350 (portrait), 
while Stories and Reels require 1080 x 1920 pixels (9:16). 

Use PNG for high-quality graphics and JPG for photos

For Video
-------------
Facebook Video Specifications

- Facebook Reels & Stories: 1080 x 1920 px (9:16 ratio).
- Facebook Feed Videos: 1080 x 1080 px (1:1) or 1080 x 1350 px (4:5) is highly effective for maximizing screen real estate.
- Horizontal Video: 1920 x 1080 px (16:9) is still supported, particularly for in-stream ads.
- File Format: .MP4 or .MOV.
- Frame Rate: 30fps is recommended.
- Maximum Length: Up to 240 minutes for standard posts.


